<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer16256329328731663516">This is Oscar Wilde&apos;s tale of the American family moved into a British mansion, Canterville Chase, much to the annoyance of its tired ghost. The family -- which refuses to believe in him -- is in Wilde&apos;s way a commentary on the British nobility of the day -- and on the Americans, too. The tale, like many of Wilde&apos;s, is rich with allusion, but ends as sentimental romance...</span>
  <span id="freeText16256329328731663516" style="display:none">This is Oscar Wilde's tale of the American family moved into a British mansion, Canterville Chase, much to the annoyance of its tired ghost. The family -- which refuses to believe in him -- is in Wilde's way a commentary on the British nobility of the day -- and on the Americans, too. The tale, like many of Wilde's, is rich with allusion, but ends as sentimental romance...</span>
