        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3235943549" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5432680493042146368">Great satire about an English ghost being outwitted by some modern Americans (Mr Otis and his family) who bought Canterville Chase. Is there salvation for the ghost in the end? Funny ghost story with many satirical elements (the bloodstain) and fine allusions (e.g. on Fuseli&apos;s Nightmare). A real classic with well drawn characters. Recommended for everybody, not only Oscar Wilde fans. </span>
  <span id="freeText5432680493042146368" style="display:none">Great satire about an English ghost being outwitted by some modern Americans (Mr Otis and his family) who bought Canterville Chase. Is there salvation for the ghost in the end? Funny ghost story with many satirical elements (the bloodstain) and fine allusions (e.g. on Fuseli's Nightmare). A real classic with well drawn characters. Recommended for everybody, not only Oscar Wilde fans. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5432680493042146368" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

