        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4163366418" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8827224844466906923">It&apos;s Oscar Wilde, of course it&apos;s going to be magnificent. <br/><br/>This short story is perfect for Halloween, a bit spooky and funny, clever, with some intricate insights about the meaning of life, death and the value of forgiveness. I enjoyed it way more than I expected and read the whole thing in one sitting. There is a few adaptions on screen, I&apos;m very curious about how the ambiance and Wilde&apos;s unique humour has been translated. <br/><br/>Recommend, recommend, recommend.</span>
  <span id="freeText8827224844466906923" style="display:none">It's Oscar Wilde, of course it's going to be magnificent. <br /><br />This short story is perfect for Halloween, a bit spooky and funny, clever, with some intricate insights about the meaning of life, death and the value of forgiveness. I enjoyed it way more than I expected and read the whole thing in one sitting. There is a few adaptions on screen, I'm very curious about how the ambiance and Wilde's unique humour has been translated. <br /><br />Recommend, recommend, recommend.</span>
